German Minister Sees Quota for Women as Last Report, Paper Says

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-02-22T07:49:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/german-minister-sees-quota-for-women-as-last-report-paper-says.html
A mandatory quota for women on
German executive and supervisory boards is a “Sword of
Damocles” that will drop if companies refuse to increase the
share of women voluntarily, German Justice Minister Sabine Leutheusser-Schnarrenberger told  Handelsblatt .  The Justice Ministry is examining ways to force companies
to publish how many women they employ and in which positions,
Leutheusser told the paper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rainer Buergin in Berlin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  